Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced). Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium high heat. Once the oil is hot, add the onion and cook until soft, ~{4-5%mins}, stirring occasionally. While the onion cooks, quarter the @dried apricots{40}(quartered) and peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Transfer the cooked onions to a #bowl{} and pop your pan back on medium high heat with another drizzle of oil. Add the @chicken thigh{260%g}(diced) with a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir-fry until the chicken is golden brown on the outside, ~{5%mins}, then add the cooked onion, apricots, garlic, @chermoula spice mix{1%tsp}, and @honey{15%ml}. Stir everything together and fry until the mixture starts to get a little sticky, ~{2%mins}.

Stir the @plain flour{24%g} into the pan and cook for ~{1%minute}, then pour in the @water{350%ml} and add the @chicken stock powder{1}. Bring to the boil and then reduce the heat and simmer until mixture has thickened, ~{3%mins}. Stir constantly.

Stir the @chopped kale{100%g} into the sauce. Cover with a #lid{} (or #foil{}) and simmer until the kale is tender and the chicken is cooked through, ~{5%mins}. IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle. Taste the sauce and add salt and pepper if you feel it needs it.

Transfer the mixture to an ovenproof dish and cover with the @puff pastry sheet{1/2}, trim the edges with a sharp #knife{}. Brush the pastry with a little @milk{} (or water if you don't have milk) and then sprinkle over the @sesame seeds{15%g}. Bake on the top shelf of your oven until golden brown, ~{12-15%mins}.

While the pie cooks, get your washing up done. Once cooked, spoon the pie into #bowls{}. Enjoy!

> TIP: Don't worry if the pastry doesn't cover the whole dish!